title: GRACE OF MONACO-2014 (WITH GR SUBS)
description:
Grace tou Monaco (2014)

"Grace of Monaco" (original title)

103 min  -  Biography | Drama | Romance  -  14 May 2014 (France)

Grace of Monaco is a 2014 American-French biography film about Grace Kelly, directed by Olivier Dahan. The film stars Nicole Kidman in the titular role.[3] It also features a supporting cast of Frank Langella, Parker Posey, Derek Jacobi, Paz Vega, Roger Ashton-Griffiths, Milo Ventimiglia, and Tim Roth.[4][5]

First scheduled for release at the end of November 2013, the film was then re-scheduled for March 14, 2014,[6] until being pulled from the release schedule indefinitely.[7][8] The film opened the 2014 Cannes Film Festival, playing out of competition.[9][10] Premiered in the UK on June 4th 2014 and went on general cinema release on June 6th.

The story of former Hollywood star Grace Kelly's crisis of marriage and identity, during a political dispute between Monaco's Prince Rainier III and France's Charles De Gaulle, and a looming French invasion of Monaco in the early 1960s.
